      'faq-04-00' : '#MetaHashCoin and Prospects',
      'faq-04-01' : 'What are the general differences between #MetaHash and any other Blockchain provider?',
      'faq-04-02' : 'All of the existing competitors are either slow or centralized. The next generation of Blockchains must be swift, totally decentralized and have cheap transactions as well. There is no existing project (except for #MetaHash) which covers all these requirements.',
      'faq-04-03' : 'Is #MHC ERC20 emited though the ETH Smart Contract?',
      'faq-04-04' : '#MHC is a separate independent coin that is operated in a separate chain. Nevertheless, some mirror contracts in Ethereum and #MetaHash exist. These mirror contracts allow for the tokenizing procedure of ERC20 tokens in both directions.',
      'faq-04-05' : 'What is the total supply in tokens?',
      'faq-04-06' : '92,000,000 #MHC will be released over a term of 10 years. 46,000,000 #MHC will be released in the first year.',
      'faq-04-07' : 'What exchange platforms will trade the #MetaHashCoins?',
      'faq-04-08' : 'Coin availability on exchange platforms will be announced through the all official #MetaHash public channels. We are not allowed to share such information in advance.',
      'faq-04-09' : 'What will the initial price of the #MHC be after the ICO once it reaches the open market? And after one year?',
      'faq-04-10' : 'The cost of #MetaHashCoin is determined by market necessities. #MHC is used to pay for the following services: transactions, data storage, app functioning and so on. These factors will influence the cost of #MHC.',
      'faq-04-11' : 'When does the token sale start/end?',
      'faq-04-12' : 'We plan to finish ICO Round A by the end of 2018. Official ICO Round B will start in Q4 of 2018 or in Q1 of 2019.',


